metadata.label: raw_orders
metadata.comment: This gem reads in raw order data from a CSV file and creates a DataFrame with a specified schema. The schema includes fields for order ID, customer ID, order status, order category, order date, and amount. This allows for easy manipulation and analysis of the order data within the Spark environment.

metadata.label: ReformatIRS
metadata.comment: This gem reformats IRS data by selecting specific columns and renaming them for easier analysis and reporting. The selected columns include information on state, zip code, income, tax deductions, and various tax credits. This could be useful for tax planning, policy analysis, and research on income inequality.

metadata.label: raw_irs_zipcode
metadata.comment: This gem reads in a CSV file containing IRS tax data by zip code and aggregates it into a Spark DataFrame. The schema is defined explicitly using StructType and StructField, and the CSV file is read in using the spark.read method with options for header and separator. This DataFrame can be used for further analysis and insights into tax data by zip code.

metadata.label: ReformatOrders
metadata.comment: This gem reformats the data types of the order_id, customer_id, order_date, and amount fields to their appropriate data types. This ensures data consistency and accuracy, and makes it easier to perform calculations and analyses on the data.

metadata.label: ReformatCustomers
metadata.comment: This gem reformats customer data by casting the customer_id and account_open_date fields to their respective data types. It also concatenates the first name and last name fields into a single full name field. This could improve data quality and consistency, and make it easier for business users to work with the data.

metadata.label: bronze_orders
metadata.comment: This gem writes the input DataFrame to a Delta Lake table named "bronze_orders" in the "scottdemo" database. This could be used for data storage and management, and to enable efficient querying and analysis of the payment data.

metadata.label: raw_customers
metadata.comment: This gem reads in a CSV file containing customer data and creates a Spark DataFrame with the specified schema. The CSV file is located in a DBFS directory and is read in using the specified options for header, separator, and schema. This provides a way to easily access and manipulate customer data within a Spark environment.

metadata.label: bronze_customers
metadata.comment: This gem writes the input DataFrame to a Delta table named "bronze_customers" in the "scottdemo" database. This could be used as a staging area for further data processing and analysis.

metadata.label: bronze_irs_zipcode
metadata.comment: This gem saves the input DataFrame as a Delta table in the `bronze_irs_zipcode` table in the `scottdemo` database. This could be used for data warehousing and data lake purposes, enabling efficient querying and analysis of the data.
